description.narrative: Under the MULU Prevention II program USAID is helping Ethiopia reduce its HIV prevalence rate by 50 percent by 2015. The program specifically seeks to strengthen HIV/AIDS responses in and around large workplaces in nine regions, especially in the areas of construction, farming and agriculture, leather processing and textile manufacturing.The overall goal of the project is to decrease the number of new HIV infections by reducing risks and vulnerability to new infections through an evidence-based process. The project contributes to the national target of reducing new infections by 50% by 2014.
